Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). Halve the @bell pepper{1}, remove the core and seeds, thinly slice, then chop the slices into 3 pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}). Zest and halve the @lime{1}. Pop the @beef strips{240%g} in a #bowl{} with the lime zest and half the @Mexican style spice mix{1}(divided). Add the @olive oil{2%tbsp} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Mix well, set aside.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #saucepan{} on high heat. When hot, add the pepper pieces and a pinch of salt and pepper. Fry until charred, ~{4-5%minutes}, stirring very occasionally, so the peppers get some colour on them. Once charred, remove from the pan to a bowl and set aside. Put the pan back on the heat, reduce the heat to medium.

Add a drizzle of oil if the pan is dry. When hot, add the onion, fry until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}, stirring occasionally. Add the @tomato puree{30%g}, garlic and remaining Mexican spice. Cook, stirring for ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @basmati rice{150%g} and pour in the @water{300%ml}, the @chicken stock powder{1} and the charred peppers. Stir everything together, and bring to the boil. Lower the heat to medium, pop a #lid{} on the pan and leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

6-7 mins before your rice is ready, pop a #frying pan{} on medium high heat (no oil). While the pan gets hot, squeeze the lime juice into a large bowl, add the @honey{15%g} and stir together. Once the pan is really hot, add the steak strips and stir-fry until browned on the outside, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The steak is cooked when brown on the outside.

Remove the strips to the bowl with the honey and lime. Stir to coat, then set aside for a couple of mins.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{}, then stir in the steak along with all the resting juices in the bowl to the rice. Taste and add salt and pepper if you feel it needs it. Spoon into #bowls{}. Enjoy!